snippet: Jenelle Kohanchuk scored twice and Vicki Bendus had the tiebreaking goal to help Canada win the Four Nations Cup tournament, 6-3, over Finland.
abstract: Canada defeats Finland, 6-3, to wins women's hockey's Four Nations Cup in Lake Placid, NY.
lead_paragraph: Jenelle Kohanchuk scored twice and Vicki Bendus had the tiebreaking goal to help Canada win the Four Nations Cup tournament, 6-3, over Finland.
